            <p:rationale>Users tend to choose simple passwords and then over-use them, which greatly increases the security risk for all systems. By defining a policy for passwords, one can prevent the main risks surrounding the misuse of passwords.</p:rationale>
            <p:implications>A standard password policy is pre-defined. There is a standard authorization facility in which this password policy is configured. Applications make maximum use of the standard authorization facility or are otherwise at least configured with password policy. The identities for administrators in applications also need the password policy requirements. Default systems passwords intended for administrators are always immediately replaced by a specific password during installation.</p:implications>
